<br>
BD and Gold makes a mask with good resists<br>
BD and Vellium makes a Bracelet with good resists<br>
BD and Platinum makes a Tiara with good resists<br>
<br>
BD is also used in cultural armor, so, your Druid might benefit more from a cultural chest piece both in AC, stats and resists than from a piece of jewelry.  However, I don't know your monk or druids races or goals, and thus don't know which way to point you.<br>
<br>
As for gear, I can't speak directly but generally I lean towards aiding my primary stats first, and resists second.  However, if you are planning on hunting dragons as a full time occupation, you will want to change that.  But, for specifics, I'be a fool to try and speak to something I don't know, so, I'll let the good druids and monks of these boards speak to that.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In short: go shopping at EQTraders.  Between this board, LDs board and the SW board, there are ample numbers of GM tradeskillers to cover most anything you want made when you do make up your mind.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ... OH!  Note what is needed for what you want to make at EQTraders to get an idea of costs: Vellium is 262p per bar at best charisma/faction, Platinum is 105p per bar at best charisma/faction, temper you will have to price out (should you decide on BD armor), etc.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
